  "title": "Submarine Service Engineer",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities:</p><ul><li>Carry out daily hands-on maintenance and inspections to ensure all assigned tasks are completed in accordance with service requirements, safety standards, and SUBSAFE procedures.</li><li>Perform troubleshooting and rectification of mechanical and marine diesel systems, including removal, servicing, installation, and system tightness testing.</li><li>Conduct joint inspections and acceptance with ship representatives, and coordinate with ship crews to perform functional testing of ship systems.</li><li>Execute replenishment of submarine supplies, including gases, fuel oil, lubricating oil, and hydraulic oil.</li></ul><p>Requirements:</p><ul><li>Preferably at least 3 years of relevant working experience; candidates without prior experience are welcome as training will be provided.</li><li>Proficient in the use of mechanical tools and equipment including spanners, ratchet wrenches, lever blocks, and chain hoists.</li><li>Able to read and interpret technical documents such as 2D assembly drawings and schematic diagrams.</li></ul><p>Interested candidates who wish to apply for the advertised position, please click on the APPLY button below to send in your resume.</p><p>EA License No: 13C6305</p><p>Reg. No.: R22104949 KOH SHI MIN, JOAN (XU SHIMIN)</p><p>For candidates who applied for the advertised position is deemed to have consented to us that we may collect, use or disclose your personal information for purpose in connection with the services provided by us.</p>",
